gomodel:SYNGO_2332  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Overexpression of SALM2 Leads to Increases in the Number of Excitatory Synapses and Dendritic Spines\"\nFig.5: \"Mislocalized Expression of SALM2 Disrupts Excitatory Synapses and Dendritic Spines\"\nFig.6: \"Direct Aggregation of SALM2 Induces Clustering of Excitatory Postsynaptic Proteins\"\nFig.7: \"Knockdown of SALM2 by siRNA Leads to the Loss of Morphological and Functional Excitatory Synapses\". Experimental description: Dissociated culture is of rat species: \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day (E) 18-19 rat hippocampi described previously.\"\n\n15/01/2018 Pim\n- Overexpressed SALM2 is of rat species: \". Full-length rat SALM2 (aa 1-766) was PCR-amplified from a rat brain cDNA library\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2332" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

